  "title": "Methods Analyst (Associate to Senior)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>This position is responsible for creating accurate and routine manufacturing sequences whereby raw materials and assemblies are processed into quality finished products using the most economical and efficient means.</li>\n  <li>Work performed requires application of standard techniques, procedures, and criteria.</li>\n  <li>Reviews prints and requirements of items to be manufactured and determines the process plans/routings, instructions, methods, procedures, tooling, etc. required.</li>\n  <li>Uses computerized files/systems to analyze production status and creates manufacturing process for parts/assembly by specifying machines to be utilized, stages of manufacture, and routing stages required to produce finished part.</li>\n  <li>Establishes standard production times for parts and/or assemblies, recommends improvements/modifications, and discusses/resolves impact of process plans with other departments as required.</li>\n  <li>2-4 years of related manufacturing engineering experience.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
